<id>https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=118&amp;p=531#p531</id>
<link href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=118&amp;p=531#p531"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Global attribute suggestion: for]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=118&amp;p=531#p531"><![CDATA[
With citations, the source can be accociated. This can be used by document conversion or with javascript extension as mouseover content (like a &quot;formated&quot; title).<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>...<br />&lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;blockquote for=&quot;cite1&quot;&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit&lt;/blockqoute&gt;<br />&lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;blockquote for=&quot;cite1&quot;&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit&lt;/blockqoute&gt;<br />&lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;blockquote for=&quot;cite2&quot;&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit, sed diam nonummy nibh euismod tincidunt ut laoreet dolore magna aliquam erat volutpat.&lt;/blockqoute&gt;<br />...</code></dd></dl><br /><br />And then, in another place of the document:<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;ul&gt;<br />&lt;li&gt;&lt;cite id=&quot;cite1&quot;&gt;From the book blindtext by John Doe&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br />&lt;li&gt;&lt;cite id=&quot;cite2&quot;&gt;From the book blindtext in the depth by John Doe&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br />&lt;/ul&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />Using it like the W3C-example for &lt;cite&gt;:<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>As &lt;CITE id=&quot;HarrySTruman&quot; &gt;Harry S. Truman&lt;/CITE&gt; said,<br />&lt;Q lang=&quot;en-us&quot; for=&quot;HarrySTruman&quot;&gt;The buck stops here.&lt;/Q&gt;<br />He said also &lt;Q lang=&quot;en-us&quot; for=&quot;HarrySTruman&quot;&gt;Good Evening, My Fellow Americans&lt;/Q&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />A combination of &lt;article&gt; and &lt;form&gt;. The &lt;article&gt; may be able to set the focus on the form.<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;article for=&quot;downloadLogin&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;To get the software you must login&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/article&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />And then, in another place of the document:<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;form id=&quot;downloadLogin&quot;&gt;... Login ...&lt;/form&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />An image description can be combinded with a text. This can be used for more accesibility and to parse documents in a microformats way.<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;img id=&quot;myImage&quot; src=&quot;people.gif&quot; alt=&quot;people&quot;&gt;<br />&lt;p for=&quot;myImage&quot;&gt;This is John Doe on the convention&lt;/p&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />With an additional relation to an &lt;article&gt;, you can parse the related content, for example if you want to change the page layout and you have to retrieve the content inherit from design.<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;section&gt;<br />&lt;article id=&quot;convention&quot;&gt;<br />&lt;h1&gt;The convention&lt;/h1&gt;<br />&lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;/article&gt;<br />&lt;/section&gt;<br /><br />&lt;aside for=&quot;convention&quot;&gt;<br />&lt;img id=&quot;myImage&quot; src=&quot;people.gif&quot; alt=&quot;people&quot;&gt;<br />&lt;p for=&quot;myImage&quot;&gt;This is John Doe on the convention&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;/aside&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />A usecase with microformats:<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;article&gt;Hello, I'm &lt;span for=&quot;commerceNet&quot;&gt;John Doe&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/article&gt;<br /><br />&lt;aside id=&quot;commerceNet&quot; class=&quot;vcard&quot;&gt;<br />  &lt;a class=&quot;fn org url&quot; href=&quot;http://www.commerce.net/&quot;&gt;CommerceNet&lt;/a&gt;<br />  &lt;div class=&quot;adr&quot;&gt;<br />    &lt;span class=&quot;type&quot;&gt;Work&lt;/span&gt;:<br />    &lt;div class=&quot;street-address&quot;&gt;169 University Avenue&lt;/div&gt;<br />    &lt;span class=&quot;locality&quot;&gt;Palo Alto&lt;/span&gt;,<br />    &lt;abbr class=&quot;region&quot; title=&quot;California&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/abbr&gt;<br />    &lt;span class=&quot;postal-code&quot;&gt;94301&lt;/span&gt;<br />    &lt;div class=&quot;country-name&quot;&gt;USA&lt;/div&gt;<br />  &lt;/div&gt;<br />  &lt;div class=&quot;tel&quot;&gt;<br />   &lt;span class=&quot;type&quot;&gt;Work&lt;/span&gt; +1-650-289-4040<br />  &lt;/div&gt;<br />  &lt;div class=&quot;tel&quot;&gt;<br />    &lt;span class=&quot;type&quot;&gt;Fax&lt;/span&gt; +1-650-289-4041<br />  &lt;/div&gt;<br />  &lt;div&gt;Email:<br />   &lt;span class=&quot;email&quot;&gt;info@commerce.net&lt;/span&gt;<br />  &lt;/div&gt;<br />&lt;/aside&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />There are several usecases: semantic relations, setting a focus, hightlight related elements, formated &quot;titles&quot; instead of title attribute, retrieve related data. In opposite to &lt;a&gt; anchors, it must not be a link and you can used it with nearly each element.<br /><br />I don't know how existing UAs handle a for-attribute outside of &lt;label&gt;. &quot;for&quot; is a well-known attribute name, but if it don't work, it must be renamed, for example to &quot;iref&quot; (inline reference).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=195">haka</a> — Sat Dec 22, 2007 5:45 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
